        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10458790" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3058687583921288635">I love this book. Love, love, love, love, love, love. Love. <br/><br/>First, it takes place on Long Island, which I didn&apos;t even know when I ordered it for the library. So, sure I got an extra chuckle out of Schmidt&apos;s description of LI in November than the reader from, say, Nebraska will. But still, this is just an adorable story and you don&apos;t have to be stuck on the Long Island Expressway to enoy it. It reminds me of Richard Peck, if Richard Peck wrote about 1960&apos;s surburban life and not 1930&apos;s Illinois. </span>
  <span id="freeText3058687583921288635" style="display:none">I love this book. Love, love, love, love, love, love. Love. <br /><br />First, it takes place on Long Island, which I didn't even know when I ordered it for the library. So, sure I got an extra chuckle out of Schmidt's description of LI in November than the reader from, say, Nebraska will. But still, this is just an adorable story and you don't have to be stuck on the Long Island Expressway to enoy it. It reminds me of Richard Peck, if Richard Peck wrote about 1960's surburban life and not 1930's Illinois. <br /><br />It is heartfelt and hopeful without being hokey. A must-read.</span>
